abstract: >
  A four-stage automated pipeline that converts French-language industrial cosmetic
  ingredient name strings into machine-learning-ready molecular descriptor matrices.
  Stage 0 applies a 274-entry domain-specific French trade name synonym dictionary;
  Stage A applies exact matching against the EU CosIng database (24,094 entries);
  Stage B applies fuzzy token-sorted Levenshtein matching (threshold ≥ 82);
  Stage C provides an optional LLM fallback. The pipeline achieves 100% INCI coverage
  on a 303-ingredient industrial corpus and 80.5% on Open Beauty Facts validation data,
  producing complete RDKit (208) and Mordred (970) descriptor matrices for 93 unique molecules.
keywords:
